Spain’s Salgado Says Talks With Banks Needed on Writedowns

-- B y   P a t r i c k   H e n r y
-- 
2011-10-21T19:48:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/spain-s-salgado-says-talks-with-banks-needed-on-writedowns.html
Spanish Economy Minister  Elena
Salgado  said talks are needed with banks on plans to increase
bondholder losses in a second rescue program for  Greece .  “I think we have to discuss with the private sector and
see what is suitable,” she told reporters in Brussels today
after a meeting of euro area finance chiefs.  Ministers discussed investor losses of “more than 21
percent,” she said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Patrick Henry  at 
 phenry8@bloomberg.net  